Job Title:     Manager Biostatistics
Job Location:  MO: Saint Louis
Pay Rate:      Open
Job Length:    full time
Start Date:    2007-12-31

Company Name:  The Cambridge Group Ltd.
Contact:       Stephanie Oscar
Phone:         E-mail or fax only
Fax:           203-226-3856

Description:   The Manager/Associate Director will provide statistical support and advocate statistical thinking to nonclinical areas of R&amp;D, including Discovery, Pharmaceutical Sciences, and Global Manufacturing organizations.   Collaborate with scientists to plan meaningful experimental studies, statistically analyze study data, and communicate results.  Provide statistical support for interactions with contract laboratories and European, Japanese and U.S. regulators.  Specific projects involve: In vivo - in vitro bioassay development / validation as markers of preclinical drug activity; safety testing and product release; In vivo - in vitro bioassay development / validation for the determination of relative potency for release testing of large molecular weight biological compounds.  Provide statistical support for manufacturing processes including Statistical Process Control and DOE.  Perform statistical analyses of study results, write summary reports and present orally.   Monitor literature for new statistical methodology and apply or adapt as appropriate.  Develop and deliver statistical training modules. Requirements:  strong science background with good working knowledge of biology, chemistry, engineering, or pharmacology; good computational skills in SAS, S-plus or R.  A MS with 5 years or a PhD with 3 years experience is necessary.

Please refer to Job code TV5029 when responding to this ad.

